casaCmQueryMib.description: This is the enterprise MIB Module for CASA systems CMTS.

TenthdBmV.name: TenthdBmV
TenthdBmV.description: This data type represents power levels that are normally expressed in dBmV. Units are in tenths of a dBmV; for example, 5.1 dBmV will be represented as 51.

TenthdB.name: TenthdB
TenthdB.description: This data type represents power levels that are normally expressed in dB. Units are in tenths of a dB; for example, 5.1 dB will be represented as 51.

casaCmQueryTable.name: casaCmQueryTable
casaCmQueryTable.description: describes the PHY signal quality and Tx/Rx parameter of cable modem.

casaCmQueryEntry.name: casaCmQueryEntry
casaCmQueryEntry.description: describes the PHY signal quality and Tx/Rx parameter of cable modem,index of this table is casaQueryCmMacAddress.

casaQueryCmTxTimeOffset.name: casaQueryCmTxTimeOffset
casaQueryCmTxTimeOffset.description: A measure of the current round trip time at the CM, or the maximum round trip time seen by the CMTS. Used for timing of CM upstream transmissions to ensure synchronized arrivals at the CMTS. Units are in terms of (6.25 microseconds/64).

casaQueryCmMicroReflection.name: casaQueryCmMicroReflection
casaQueryCmMicroReflection.description: Total microreflections including in-channel response as perceived on this interface, measured in dBc below the signal level. This object is not assumed to return an absolutely accurate value, but should give a rough indication of microreflections received on this interface. It is up to the implementor to provide information as accurate as possible.

casaQueryCmStatusTxPower.name: casaQueryCmStatusTxPower
casaQueryCmStatusTxPower.description: The operational transmit power of the cable modem downstream channel,the most current value (CM) or the value of 0.

casaQueryCmStatusRxPower.name: casaQueryCmStatusRxPower
casaQueryCmStatusRxPower.description: The operational receive power of the cable modem upstream channel,the most current value (CM) or the value of 0

casaQueryCmSigQSignalNoise.name: casaQueryCmSigQSignalNoise
casaQueryCmSigQSignalNoise.description: Signal/Noise ratio as perceived for this channel. describes the Signal/Noise of the upstream channel of CM .

casaQueryCmtsSigQSignalNoise.name: casaQueryCmtsSigQSignalNoise
casaQueryCmtsSigQSignalNoise.description: Signal/Noise ratio as perceived for this channel. describes the average Signal/Noiseof the upstream channel of CMTS.

casaCmQueryroup.name: casaCmQueryroup
casaCmQueryroup.description: Box is required to support objects in this group
